.TH DBX-VERIFY 1 "2026-06-02" "dbx 0.28.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-verify \- verify a backup's checksum and inspect its sidecar
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx verify
.I backup-file
.SH DESCRIPTION
Verify that the SHA-256 checksum of
.I backup-file
matches the value recorded in its
.IR .meta.json
sidecar. Prints the file size, source flavor / version, and
.B dbx
version at write time.
.PP
.I backup-file
may be an absolute path or a relative path under
.IR $DATA_DIR .
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
dbx verify ~/.data/dbx/prod/myapp/myapp_20260524_120000.sql.zst
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Checksum matches; the backup is intact.
.TP
non-zero
Checksum mismatch, sidecar missing, or the file isn't a recognizable
dbx backup.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR dbx-list (1),
.BR dbx-restore (1).
